This paper deals with a problem in data analysis related to sampling in the presence of joins. Therefore, it is likely to belong to the database (cs.DB) and data structures (cs.DS) categories. Additionally, the paper proposes techniques for achieving randomness in sampling, which is a common problem in machine learning (cs.AI) and statistics (cs.LG). Finally, the paper also discusses enhancements to algorithms, which could fall under the information theory (cs.IT) category.
